                    <abstract lang="eng">Question answering systems provide easy access to structured data, in particular RDF data. However, the user experience is often negatively aï¬€ected by questions that are not interpreted correctly. To remedy this, we present a new guided approach to QA that ensures that all questions that can be entered into the system also return a corresponding answer. For this, a template-based approach is used to generate all possible questions from a given RDF dataset using a number of templates. The question/answer pairs can then be indexed to provide autocompletion functionality at querying time. We describe the architecture and approach and present preliminary evaluation results.</abstract>
